From 98db3dcb04b3cdb635f9f9843636aefb2f26a8e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Aug 2025 19:20:29 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: CP: wifi: ath12k: Use link config MAC for scan vdev

Currently, a separate vdev is created with link ID
ATH12K_DEFAULT_SCAN_LINK (15) for scanning, which uses a randomly
generated MAC address. However, active scanning requires the
configured MAC address, typically associated with link ID 0 in
vif->link_conf.

Use MAC address from link ID 0 for scan vdev in station mode

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -15524,6 +15524,9 @@ int ath12k_mac_vdev_create(struct ath12k
 	 */
 	if (arvif->link_id >= ATH12K_DEFAULT_SCAN_LINK && vif->valid_links)
 		link_id = ffs(vif->valid_links) - 1;
+	else if (arvif->link_id == ATH12K_DEFAULT_SCAN_LINK &&
+		 vif->type == NL80211_IFTYPE_STATION)
+		link_id = 0;
 	else
 		link_id = arvif->link_id;
 
